Senior officials in Justice Mogoeng’s office told Parliament on Wednesday security had been tightened following the break-in that led to the theft of 15 computers with personal information of the country’s 250 judges. Two people were arrested in Pretoria for the incident and have since appeared in court. Memme Sejosengwe, secretary-general in the Office of the Chief Justice, said the matter was still under investigation. But police have already increased patrols in the building. The number of security guards was increased and more CCTV cameras and lights had been installed, Sejosengwe said. Political Bureau